Field.Name: ALL
Field.Description: All terms from all searchable fields

Field.Name: UID
Field.Description: Unique number assigned to each sequence

Field.Name: ORGN
Field.Description: Scientific and common names of organism, and all higher levels of taxonomy

Field.Name: PACC
Field.Description: Does not include retired secondary accessions

Field.Name: GENE
Field.Description: Name of gene associated with sequence

Field.Name: PROT
Field.Description: Name of protein associated with sequence

Field.Name: ECNO
Field.Description: EC number for enzyme or CAS registry number

Field.Name: SUBS
Field.Description: CAS chemical name or MEDLINE Substance Name

Field.Name: PROP
Field.Description: Classification by source qualifiers and molecule type

Field.Name: PORG
Field.Description: Scientific and common names of primary organism, and all higher levels of taxonomy

Link.Name: nuccore_assembly
Link.Description: Corresponding assembly of the individual sequence traces from the Trace Assembly Archive for the current sequence records. The assembly is available as a graphical display of the trace components.

Link.Name: nuccore_bioproject
Link.Description: Related BioProject entry

Link.Name: nuccore_biosample
Link.Description: BioSample links

Link.Name: nuccore_biosystems
Link.Description: BioSystems

Link.Name: nuccore_comp_nuccore
Link.Description: Assembled nucleotide records constructed from the current component sequences (whole genome shotgun, genomic scaffolds, and BAC clone sequences).

Link.Name: nuccore_dbvar
Link.Description: Genomic structural variation (dbVar) records that refer to the current nucleotide sequence records.

Link.Name: nuccore_gene
Link.Description: Gene records referencing the current sequence records. Sequences included in Gene are added manually by NCBI.

Link.Name: nuccore_genome
Link.Description: Genome records related to the current sequence records. Genome records may be linked to the components of assembled genome and from single record submissions representing complete genomic molecules such as chromosomes, organelle genomes, and plasmids.

Link.Name: nuccore_genome_samespecies
Link.Description: Reference genome records for the same species as the current nucleotide genomic records. These genomes represent a single version for multiple variable sequences of the same genomic molecule, most commonly viral and organelle genomes.

Link.Name: nuccore_gensat
Link.Description: Gensat records that use the mRNAs or genes corresponding to the current records as probes or reporter constructs in mouse brain histology imaging.

Link.Name: nuccore_geoprofiles
Link.Description: GEO Profile records associated with Nucleotide record

Link.Name: nuccore_homologene
Link.Description: Homologene clusters that contain the current RefSeq transcript sequences.

Link.Name: nuccore_mapview
Link.Description: Graphical Map Viewer display of the current nucleotide records in assembled genomes. Records may be part of the assembly or mapped as alignment-based annotation.

Link.Name: nuccore_mrna_nuccore
Link.Description: Genomic sequence records that have the current mRNA records as annotated features marking the exons of genes.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore
Link.Description: Nucleotide sequences related by sequence similarity (BLAST) score to the current records.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_comp
Link.Description: Nucleotide records that are the components of the assembled sequence records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_gbrs
Link.Description: NCBI Reference Sequence genomic records that are identical in sequence to records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_mgc_refseq
Link.Description: Order cDNA clone corresponding to Mammalian Gene Collection Reference Sequence records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_mrna
Link.Description: mRNA sequence records that are annotated on the current genomic nucleotide sequences. The mRNA records represent aligned or predicted transcripts of the current records.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_rsgb
Link.Description: Identical source nucleotide records to Reference Sequence assembled genomes in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_samespecies_gbrs
Link.Description: NCBI Reference Sequence (RefSeq) genome record for the same species as the current International Nucleotide Database Collaboration (DDBJ, EMBL, GenBank) genomic records. These RefSeq genomes represent a single version for multiple variable sequences of the same genomic molecule, most commonly viral and organelle genomes.

Link.Name: nuccore_nuccore_samespecies_rsgb
Link.Description: Other nucleotide records for the same molecule in the same species for genome records in the current set. These are linked from the GenBank source record for the genome Reference Sequence. These linked records are available when there are multiple other records for the same genomic sequence in the database. Most commonly these are microbial, organelle, or viral genomes.

Link.Name: nuccore_nucest_comp
Link.Description: Expressed Sequence Tag (EST) records that are components of assembled nucleotide records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_nucgss_comp
Link.Description: Genome Survey Sequence (GSS) records that are components of the assembled nucleotide records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_omim
Link.Description: Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man articles that refer to nucleotide records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_pcassay
Link.Description: BioAssay records that refer to nucleotide records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_pcassay_rna_target
Link.Description: BioAssays that refer to records in the current set as mRNA targets.

Link.Name: nuccore_pccompound
Link.Description: PubChem compound records that cite the nucleotide records in the current set. These compound records are typically associated with nucleotide sequence through a molecular structure containing the both the nucleic acid and the PubChem small molecule.

Link.Name: nuccore_pcsubstance
Link.Description: PubChem substance records that cite the nucleotide records in the current set. These substance records may be associated with a nucleotide sequence through a molecular structure containing the both the nucleic acid and the PubChem small molecule or may be the target of the substance entry for an inhibitory RNA Bioassay.

Link.Name: nuccore_pmc
Link.Description: Free full-text articles in PubMed central that cite nucleotide records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_popset
Link.Description: Population, ecosystem, or phylogenetic sets in the PopSet database that include records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_probe
Link.Description: Probe database records for genotyping, gene expression, SNP discovery, genome mapping, and gene silencing reagents that target the genes and gene products associated with the current nucleotide sequence records.

Link.Name: nuccore_protein
Link.Description: Protein translations of coding regions from sequence records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_protein_mat_peptide
Link.Description: Protein records for mature (processed) peptides annotated on nucleotide records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_protein_mgc_url
Link.Description: Order cDNA clones corresponding to Mammalian Gene Collection records in the current set that include the complete protein coding region.

Link.Name: nuccore_protein_wgs
Link.Description: Protein translations of coding regions from whole genome shotgun derived nucleotide sequences in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_proteinclusters
Link.Description: Protein cluster records containing proteins derived from coding regions on Reference Sequence genomic records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_pubmed
Link.Description: PubMed articles that cite nucleotide records in the current set. These are articles that report the International Nucleotide Database Collaboration (DDBJ, EMBL, GenBank) data. These articles are also linked to Reference Sequences derived from these records.

Link.Name: nuccore_pubmed_refseq
Link.Description: PubMed articles that are cited in NCBI Reference Sequences in the present set.

Link.Name: nuccore_pubmed_weighted
Link.Description: PubMed articles associated with the current nucleotide records through the Gene database. These articles include Reference into Function, citations in related OMIM, and those associated with sequences in the Gene record.

Link.Name: nuccore_snp
Link.Description: Single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) mapped to the current records. Links may be provided through SNP data submission or through annotations on the nucleotide record.

Link.Name: nuccore_snp_genegenotype
Link.Description: Genotype reports for single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) associated with the current records.

Link.Name: nuccore_snp_geneview
Link.Description: Geneview in dbSNP showing nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) mapped to the genes associated with the current records.

Link.Name: nuccore_sra
Link.Description: Sequence Read Archive (SRA) next generation sequencing data associated with the current records.

Link.Name: nuccore_sra_wgs
Link.Description: Sequence Read Archive (SRA) next generation sequencing data associated with the whole genome shotgun sequence records.

Link.Name: nuccore_structure
Link.Description: Three dimensional structure records that are the sources of the current nucleotide sequence records.

Link.Name: nuccore_taxonomy
Link.Description: NCBI Taxonomy entries and classification information for the source organisms of the current set of records.

Link.Name: nuccore_trace
Link.Description: Trace archive capillary sequencing data supporting the current nucleotide records.

Link.Name: nuccore_unigene
Link.Description: UniGene clusters of expressed sequences that contain mRNA records in the current set.

Link.Name: nuccore_unists
Link.Description: Genetic, physical, and sequence mapping reagents in the UniSTS database mapped on the current nucleotide records.
